##### NVT sampling of LJ fluid with the BAOAB Langevin integrator #####
#
# Demonstrates fix baoab as a standalone time integrator (no fix nve needed).
# The system is a simple LJ fluid at reduced units T=1.0, rho=0.8.

units           lj
atom_style      atomic
dimension       3
newton on

lattice         fcc 0.8442
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 1.6795962 1.6795962 1.6795962
region          box block 0 4 0 4 0 4
create_box      1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (6.7183848 6.7183848 6.7183848)
  1 by 2 by 2 MPI processor grid
create_atoms    1 box
Created 256 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (6.7183848 6.7183848 6.7183848)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.003 seconds
mass            * 1.0

velocity        all create 1.0 54321 loop geom

pair_style      lj/cut 2.5
pair_coeff      1 1 1.0 1.0 2.5

neighbor        0.3 bin
neigh_modify    delay 0 every 1 check yes

# BAOAB integrator: T=1.0, damp=1.0 (10x the timestep)
# zero yes removes net random momentum to prevent drift
fix             1 all baoab 1.0 1.0 1.0 12345 zero yes

thermo_style    custom step temp pe ke etotal press
thermo          100

timestep        0.005

# short equilibration
run             1000
